## Problem
This is an inbox example. It demonstrates that captured items live in
`.squad/items/` alongside everything else; the `status: captured` field
keeps them out of the claim queue (`squad next`) until you promote them.

## Context
Run `squad inbox` to see this item. Run `squad accept IDEA-001 --strict`
to see it fail Definition of Ready (the area is `<fill-in>`). Edit the
file to set a real area, then `squad accept IDEA-001` succeeds and the
item becomes claimable like any other.

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Try `squad inbox` to list captured items
- [ ] Try `squad accept IDEA-001` (will fail DoR initially)
- [ ] Edit the area, retry — promotion succeeds
- [ ] `squad next` now lists IDEA-001 as ready

## Notes
You can delete this example any time with `squad reject IDEA-001 --reason "demo"`.
